### [‚Äã](https://docs.solanamobile.com/react-native/first_app_tutorial\#sign-transaction/message-button)  Sign Transaction/Message Button

The `SignMessageButton` component takes in a `messageBuffer` byte array and calls `wallet.signMessages()`. This requests the
connected wallet to sign the message with the user‚Äôs private key.The `SignTransactionButton` component does several things on click. Within the wallet session, it constructs a `Transaction` with a
`SystemProgram.transfer` instruction, then requests the wallet to provide a signature in the transaction.

